==English==

===Etymology===
From a metathetic variation of {{m|en|gird||to strike, smite, upbraid, scold, jibe}}, from {{der|en|enm|girden}}, {{m|enm|gerden||to strike, thrust, smite|lit=smite with a rod}}, from {{m|enm|gerd}}, {{m|enm|yerd||a rod, yard}}. More at {{l|en|yard}}.

