===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|obsolete|transitive}} To [[pierce]] (something) with a weapon; to [[wound]], to [[stab]].
#* {{RQ:Spenser Faerie Queene|book=III|canto=I<!-- the page incorrectly says II -->|page=408|passage=Where feeling one cloſe couched by her ſide / She lightly lept out of her filed bedd, / And to her weapon ran, in minde to '''gride''' / The loathed leachour.}}
# {{lb|en|obsolete|intransitive}} To travel {{m|en|through}} something, of a weapon or sharp object.
#* {{RQ:Spenser Faerie Queene|book=II|canto=VIII|page=300-301|pageref=301|passage=So ſtoutly he withſtood their ſtrong aſſay, / Till that at laſt, when he aduantage ſpyde, / His poynant ſpeare he thruſt with puiſſant ſway / At proud ''Cymochles,'' whiles his ſhield was wyde, / That through his thigh the mortall ſteele did '''gryde'''{{...}}}}
# To produce a [[grind]]ing or [[scrape|scraping]] sound.
#* '''1849''', {{w|Alfred, Lord Tennyson}}, ''{{w|In Memoriam A.H.H.}}'', canto 108:
#*: Fiercely flies<br>The blast of North and East, and ice<br>Makes daggers at the sharpen’d eaves,<br>And bristles all the brakes and thorns<br>To yon hard crescent, as she hangs<br>Above the wood which '''grides''' and clangs<br>Its leafless ribs and iron horns<br>Together, in the drifts that pass<br>To darken on the rolling brine<br>That breaks the coast.

